<HL>
   Business Brief -- Borden Inc.:
   Food-Service Unit to Build
   `Hyperplant' in Pennsylvania
</HL>
<DATE>
08/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BN
</CO>
<LP>
   Borden Inc., New York, said it plans to build a $25
million "hyperplant" in Chambersburg, Pa., for its
food-service group to produce individual serving products and
bulk-size oil-based items.
   Production at the plant is scheduled for the second
quarter of 1991 and full operation for the next quarter.
About 400 jobs will be created at the new plant.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Borden is upgrading many of its production facilities;
food-service projects account for about $90 million of
planned capital spending of $650 million for 1990-1991. The
company makes food and nonfood consumer proucts, packaging
and industrial products.
</TEXT>
